msgid "Tamenaṃ so gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā paṇītena piṇḍapātena parivisati. "
msgstr "That householder or their child serves them with delicious alms-food. "

msgctxt "mn55:8-10.10"
msgid "Tassa na evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "It never occurs to them, "

msgctxt "mn55:8-10.11"
msgid "‘sādhu vata māyaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā paṇītena piṇḍapātena pariviseyyāti. "
msgstr "‘It’s so good that this householder serves me with delicious alms-food! "

msgctxt "mn55:8-10.12"
msgid "Aho vata māyaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā āyatimpi evarūpena paṇītena piṇḍapātena pariviseyyā’ti—"
msgstr "I hope they serve me with such delicious alms-food in the future!’ "

msgctxt "mn55:8-10.13"
msgid "evampissa na hoti. "
msgstr "They don’t think that. "

msgctxt "mn55:8-10.14"
msgid "So taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ agathito amucchito anajjhopanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati. "
msgstr "They eat that alms-food untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawback, and understanding the escape. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn55:8-10.15"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, jīvaka, "
msgstr "What do you think, Jīvaka? "

msgctxt "mn55:8-10.16"
msgid "api nu so bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye attabyābādhāya vā ceteti, parabyābādhāya vā ceteti, ubhayabyābādhāya vā cetetī”ti? "
msgstr "At that time is that mendicant intending to hurt themselves, hurt others, or hurt both?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "mn55:8-10.17"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "mn55:8-10.18"
msgid "“Nanu so, jīvaka, bhikkhu tasmiṃ samaye anavajjaṃyeva āhāraṃ āhāretī”ti? "
msgstr "“Aren’t they eating blameless food at that time?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11, pts-vp-pli1.371, sc10
msgctxt "mn55:11.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir. "

msgctxt "mn55:11.2"
msgid "Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante: "
msgstr "Sir, I have heard that "

msgctxt "mn55:11.3"
msgid "‘brahmā upekkhāvihārī’ti. "
msgstr "Brahmā abides in equanimity. "

msgctxt "mn55:11.4"
msgid "Taṃ me idaṃ, bhante, bhagavā sakkhidiṭṭho; "
msgstr "Now, I’ve seen the Buddha with my own eyes, "

msgctxt "mn55:11.5"
msgid "bhagavā hi, bhante, upekkhāvihārī”ti. "
msgstr "and it is the Buddha who truly abides in equanimity.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn55:11.6"
msgid "“Yena kho, jīvaka, rāgena yena dosena yena mohena vihesavā assa arativā assa paṭighavā assa so rāgo so doso so moho tathāgatassa pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo. "
msgstr "“Any greed, hate, or delusion that might give rise to cruelty, negativity, or repulsion has been given up by the Realized One, cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and is unable to arise in the future. "

msgctxt "mn55:11.7"
msgid "Sace kho te, jīvaka, idaṃ sandhāya bhāsitaṃ, anujānāmi te etan”ti. "
msgstr "If that’s what you were referring to, I acknowledge it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn55:11.8"
msgid "“Etadeva kho pana me, bhante, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ”. "
msgstr "“That’s exactly what I was referring to.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc11
msgctxt "mn55:12.1"
msgid "“Yo kho, jīvaka, tathāgataṃ vā tathāgatasāvakaṃ vā uddissa pāṇaṃ ārabhati so pañcahi ṭhānehi bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati. "
msgstr "“Jīvaka, anyone who slaughters a living creature specially for the Realized One or the Realized One’s disciple makes much bad karma for five reasons. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn55:12.2"
msgid "Yampi so, gahapati, evamāha: "
msgstr "When they say: "

msgctxt "mn55:12.3"
msgid "‘gacchatha, amukaṃ nāma pāṇaṃ ānethā’ti, iminā paṭhamena ṭhānena bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati. "
msgstr "‘Go, fetch that living creature,’ this is the first reason. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn55:12.4"
msgid "Yampi so pāṇo galappaveṭhakena ānīyamāno dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, iminā dutiyena ṭhānena bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati. "
msgstr "When that living creature experiences pain and sadness as it’s led along by a collar, this is the second reason. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn55:12.5"
msgid "Yampi so evamāha: "
msgstr "When they say: "

msgctxt "mn55:12.6"
msgid "‘gacchatha imaṃ pāṇaṃ ārabhathā’ti, iminā tatiyena ṭhānena bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati. "
msgstr "‘Go, slaughter that living creature,’ this is the third reason. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn55:12.7"
msgid "Yampi so pāṇo ārabhiyamāno dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, iminā catutthena ṭhānena bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati. "
msgstr "When that living creature experiences pain and sadness as it’s being slaughtered, this is the fourth reason. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn55:12.8"
msgid "Yampi so tathāgataṃ vā tathāgatasāvakaṃ vā akappiyena āsādeti, iminā pañcamena ṭhānena bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavati. "
msgstr "When they provide the Realized One or the Realized One’s disciple with unallowable food, this is the fifth reason. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn55:12.9"
msgid "Yo kho, jīvaka, tathāgataṃ vā tathāgatasāvakaṃ vā uddissa pāṇaṃ ārabhati so imehi pañcahi ṭhānehi bahuṃ apuññaṃ pasavatī”ti. "
msgstr "Anyone who slaughters a living creature specially for the Realized One or the Realized One’s disciple makes much bad karma for five reasons.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, sc12
msgctxt "mn55:13.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, jīvako komārabhacco bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, Jīvaka said to the Buddha: "

msgctxt "mn55:13.2"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! "

msgctxt "mn55:13.3"
msgid "Kappiyaṃ vata, bhante, bhikkhū āhāraṃ āhārenti; "
msgstr "The mendicants indeed eat allowable food. "

msgctxt "mn55:13.4"
msgid "anavajjaṃ vata, bhante, bhikkhū āhāraṃ āhārenti. "
msgstr "The mendicants indeed eat blameless food. "

msgctxt "mn55:13.5"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante … pe … "
msgstr "Excellent, sir! Excellent! … "

msgctxt "mn55:13.6"
msgid "upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn55:13.7"
msgid "Jīvakasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

